Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Pour 300ml cold @salted water{300%ml} into a #medium pot{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, lower the heat to medium, cover with the lid and cook for ~{12%minutes}.

Remove the #pot{} from the heat and keep covered for another ~{12%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

In a #bowl{}, mix @Breadcrumbs{1%pack} with @oil{2%tbsp}. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Pop the @Irish Chicken Breast{320%g} on a lined #baking tray{}. Season with salt and pepper.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken.

Spoon the @Mayo{2%sachets} over the top of the chicken.

Top with the crumb. Press down firmly with the back of a #spoon{}.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to packaging used to keep it fresh.

When the oven is hot, place the chicken on the top shelf.

Bake until cooked through and golden on top, ~{25-30%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Trim the @Broccolini{150%g}. Peel and grate the @Garlic{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

When the chicken has ~{10%minutes} of cooking time left, place a pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, fry the broccolini until starting to char, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic, lower heat to medium and cook for ~{1%minute}. Add a splash of @water{to taste} and cover with a lid or some #foil{}.

Cook until tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Remove from the pan, set aside and cover to keep warm.

Return the pan to medium-high heat.

Add the @Teriyaki Sauce{1%sachet} along with a splash of @water{to taste}.

Cook, stirring, until warmed through, ~{1%minute}.

Remove from the heat and stir through the @Sweet Chilli Sauce{1%sachet}.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and divide between plates.

Serve the pan-fried broccolini and crumbed chicken alongside.

Drizzle the tangy teriyaki sauce over the chicken and rice.